    "created_at": "2016-11-27T16:52:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-27T16:52:52Z",
    "body": "BTW: I wasn't calling `win.setFullScreen(true)` I was just passing in `{fullscreen: true}` as an option to `new BrowserWindow`\r\n\r\nMy workaround ATM is to instead pass on `{fullscreenable: true}` and then use something like\r\n\r\n```\r\n  webContents.on('dom-ready', () => {\r\n      window.setFullScreen(true);\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that if I don't pass in `{fullscreenable: true}` then `window.setFullScreen(true)` has no effect even though the docs say `{fullscreenable: true}` is the default\r\n \r\n"
  },
