    "created_at": "2017-06-01T06:20:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-06-01T23:44:28Z",
    "body": "I just submitted PR #9645 that hopefully fixes this issue. After it's merged you won't need any of the above workarounds and can just use `{ fullscreen: true }` and avoid the two step startup animation of normal->fullscreen. i.e. It should be possible to render straight to fullscreen and still have a responsive window after leaving the fullscreen state.\r\n\r\nFYI: The `WS_VISIBLE` flag wasn't being set for the `GWL_STYLE` on return to the `ui::SHOW_STATE_NORMAL` window state, thus the window couldn't receive any OS events and appeared unresponsive."
  }
